[Text engl]
{Name}{}{James}
{DescAliveShort}{}{You see a burly, thick-set man with short, bushy hair.}
{DescAliveFull}{}{You see James Hoffy, the caravan master.}
{DescAliveFull}{}{You see a scarred, tough-looking man with a calculating stare.}
{Speech 1}{}{Initial preferences}
{Speech 1 Answer 8}{}{stupid}
{Speech 1 Answer 2}{}{know}
{Speech 1 Answer 2*}{}{not know}
{Speech 2}{}{Hello there, I'm James Hoffy. But usually people call me Jimmy. I organize the caravans around here.}
{Speech 2 Answer 3}{}{Are there any caravans ready to go out now?}
{Speech 2 Answer 6}{}{Where do the caravans from Redding usually go?}
{Speech 2 Answer 7}{}{Hear any news around town lately?}
{Speech 2 Answer Exit}{}{I was just looking around, Jimmy. Thanks. Goodbye.}
{Speech 2 Answer 9}{}{There is one thing, my friend [You describe the man you have told about by undertaker] departed with your caravan a few weeks ago, I’d like to catch up to him.}
{Speech 2 Answer 10}{}{I need information concerning one of your caravans. Few week ago an unplanned traveler left with it, remember?}
{Speech 2 Answer 20}{}{Джеймс. Я один из охранников каравана Даппо.}
{Speech 2 Answer 25}{}{Джимми, есть разговор, на тему охраны караванов...}
{Speech 3}{}{That I don't know. You'd have to ask the caravan drivers. You can usually find a caravan here on the 1st, 11th, and 21st of each month. Real neat and tidy that way. You see here, this is the way it works: When a caravan's in town and looking for help, the caravan master has his tent set up here just south of my castle. Real neat and tidy that way.}
{Speech 3 Answer 4}{}{Your castle? What do you mean?}
{Speech 3 Answer Exit}{}{I see. I guess I'll talk to them, then. Thanks. Goodbye.}
{Speech 3 Answer 33}{}{А где мне найти караванщика? Где они сейчас? Здесь, в Реддинге?}
{Speech 4}{}{What else is a man's home? Sheesh, were you brought up in a tent or something?}
{Speech 4 Answer 5}{}{Actually… I was.}
{Speech 4 Answer Exit}{}{I've heard enough from you, damn bigot. Goodbye.}
{Speech 5}{}{Oh, yeah. Well, I guess that explains things, then. A lot of things. Heh, heh.}
{Speech 5 Answer 2}{}{Now that we've straightened that out, let me ask you something else.}
{Speech 5 Answer Exit}{}{Yeah. Goodbye.}
{Speech 6}{}{We run caravans all over the fricking place. Let me tell you: We've got gold ore going out to Vault City, we've got some going out to New Reno (ooo-la-la, if ya know what I mean), and we've even got some going to those prissy bastards in the NCR.}
{Speech 6 Answer 2}{}{Let me ask you about something else.}
{Speech 6 Answer Exit}{}{That's all I need to know for now. Goodbye.}
{Speech 7}{}{Not a whole lot going on lately, I guess. Just the usual digging, and caravans and stuff.}
{Speech 7 Answer 2}{}{Let me ask you about something else.}
{Speech 7 Answer Exit}{}{Yeah. Goodbye.}
{Speech 9}{}{Yes. He had this strange suit with a number, I remember. Why not, I can help you. Caravan went to San-Francisco.}
{Speech 9 Answer Exit}{}{Thanks a lot! [Leave]}
{Speech 10}{}{Heh. Any information has its price, especially concerning caravans, maybe you are some kind of bandit, how should I know. $1500 and I will show you the direction.}
{Speech 10 Answer Exit}{}{All right, I’m gonna find it n my own! [Leave]}
{Speech 10 Answer 11}{}{Here is 1000 coins. Tell me the route.}
{Speech 10 Answer 11*}{}{Here is 800 coins! Tell me the route.}
{Speech 10 Answer 11**}{}{Here is 500 coins. Tell me the route.}
{Speech 11}{}{[Smiling boldly] Very well. There is nothing you can’t do for an honest man! Caravan went to San-Francisco.}
{Speech 11 Answer Exit}{}{Your “generosity” will not be forgotten. [Leave]}
{Speech 20}{}{Да, я знаю. Благодарю за службу. Вот твои деньги.}
{Speech 20 Answer Exit}{}{ Спасибо. [Уйти]}
{Speech 20 Answer 21}{}{Джеймс, а может, накинешь немного?}
{Speech 21}{}{Нет, денег не дам, могу книжку дать, интересует?}
{Speech 21 Answer Exit}{}{Я возьму "Электронику Дина"}
{Speech 21 Answer Exit*}{}{Я возьму книгу по первой помощи.}
{Speech 21 Answer Exit**}{}{Настольная книга скаута мне пригодится.}
{Speech 21 Answer Exit***}{}{Возьму "Оружие и боеприпасы".}
{Speech 21 Answer Exit****}{}{Нет, книги мне не нужны, оставь себе. [Уйти]}
{Speech 25}{}{Да, в чем дело? Какой караван?}
